- cs.DB (Databases) is another possibility as the paper discusses the precomputing and storing of all-pairs shortest path, which involves database management.

- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also possible as the paper discusses the performance of the algorithm on a dataset about Northwest USA, which may involve network analysis.
